On May 14, a video of a police car forcing a private car to stop on the highway circulated on the Internet. The video showed that after a police car failed to overtake, it immediately sounded the siren to force the private car to stop. Later, two ununiformed personnel got out of the car to check the driver's ID and said that he "did not give way to the official vehicle and dangerously cut off the car." 
The reporter reported the situation to the Hubei Provincial Public Security Department, and the police inspection staff responded that it had been accepted and would be responded within 30 working days.
